<image 1>The sinoatrial (SA) node is indicated by ________.

A. A
B. B
C. C
D. D
E. E

The sinoatrial (SA) node, also known as the pacemaker of the heart, is located in the upper part of the right atrium near the opening of the superior vena cava. In the provided diagram, the SA node is typically located near the top of the right atrium.

Looking at the labels:
- A is near the top of the right atrium.
- B is near the middle of the right atrium.
- C is near the bottom of the right atrium.
- D and E are on the left side of the heart.

Therefore, the SA node is most likely indicated by label A.

The correct answer is:
A. A
